********** Linux vs Ubuntu ************
- Linux is not a Operating System (OS)
- Linux is karnel
- Kernel is the central part of an OS that manages the  communication between hardware and software.
- The karnel name of windows XP, vista, 7 is NT.
- The karnel name of mac is XNU.
- Ubuntu is made by canonical linux.
- The OS group which have linux karnel are called together 'Lunux Distro'.
- Different version name of ubntu:
  - Jaunty Jackalope (9.04)
  - Karmic Koala (9.10)
  - Lucid Lynx (10.04)
  - Trusty Tahr (14.04)
  - Utopic Unicorn (14.10)
  - Vivid Vervet (15.04)
  - Wily werewokf (15.10)
  - Xenial Xernus (16.04)

      karnel + (application, program, software) = Operating System

- Ubuntu is a south african word means 'humanity to others'.

- Unity desktop of ubuntu, KDE desktop of kubuntu, LXDE desktop of LUBUNTU.
- different ubuntu:
    - KDE   + UBUNTU => KUBUNTU
    - XFCE  + UBUNTU => XUMUNTU
    - LXDE  + UBUTNU => LUBUNTU

********* Terminal *************
- username@computer-name:~$  // $ means, terminal is ready for taking out commands.
- sudo => Super-user-Do  // requires password
- Keep the sudo password in memory for 15 minutes

<---- The 10-character code of death ----------->
- sudo rm -rf /

<----- some fancy commands -------->
- firefox, vlc, data, cal, df, uptime, whoami, uname, uname -a // show details all
- Linux is case-sensitive.
- man <any-command>               // show all possible command details
- ifconfig                        // show different ports, ip , mac address etc.
- whois <domain-name>             // e.g. whois www.google.com, show domain details
